            <div class="field-item odd">
                      <div class="field-label-inline-first">
              Librarian Comment:&nbsp;</div>
                    <p><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px;">Only the first 10 books of this series are found in Elder Scrolls Online. They are split into 24 volumes.&nbsp;</span></p>
<hr />
<p>Here is what Ted &quot;Tedders&quot; Peterson [some time after Morrowind] has to say about the year 1E 2921:</p>
<blockquote><p>&quot;There&#39;s no 1E 2921. The next year was CE 1 if you were living in it, or from the perspective of the third era, 2E 1.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>About the Tribunal not being able to defend Morrowind:</p>
<blockquote><p>&quot;They did use their powers to defend Morrowind from the Imperial army for four score years. Not bad. Would they have eventually triumphed? Not if Almalexia&rsquo;s vision in the first book was accurate, which Vivec didn&rsquo;t seem to doubt it.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>About the Tribunal mostly playing the role of generals:</p>
<blockquote><p>&quot;Well, you&rsquo;re only reading about two of the battles of the long war, Bodrum and Ald Marak. In those, I&rsquo;ll grant you that Vivec assumed more of the role of a general than a singular god-warrior. You can assume that he employed a variety of different roles during the course of the war.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>About Gideon appearing both as a city in Cyrodiil and as a city in Black Marsh, and about Wroth Naga apparently overlooking the Wrothgarian Mountains (despite the fact that it is in Cyrodiil and the Wrothgarian Mountains are in High Rock):</p>
<blockquote><p>&quot;I, um, must have mistranslated. Wroth Naga is in Cyrodiil and Gideon is in Black Marsh. If a new edition of the series is published in Oblivion, I&#39;ll try to make those corrections...&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="rteindent1">&nbsp;</p>
        </div>
        </div>
</div>
